Maternal school is also part of offices that have included architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint of Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also accommodate a mini school motherhood with all the necessary - colour walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, the children of the employees of Arch. design can go there.
The architectonic project company Arch. Design. whose workshops have produced a large number of buildings in Brno, has envisioned his mini-maternal business school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially from the age of children, and it was important that women architects and project leaders could quickly return to work.
At the same time as low-time employment contracts, the maternal school is a bonus offered to its employees by the company Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Manufacturers and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who imagined this mother school and with the support of management that they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-maternal school is funded through the European Social Fund through the operational programme of human resources and the State budget of the Czech Republic.
They were able to purchase equipment and equipment and after two years to provide qualified personnel and the start-up.
After the use of the funding allocation (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini-maternal school on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted for one year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to apply for staffing.
Child care is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and a nursery teacher take care of children. Children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are more than three years old for most.
As it is a "mini school motherhood" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more to replace.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of parents and children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is individual care and education, the maternal mini-school program is similar to that for preschool education.
Children do not just play it but they are also guaranteed quality education - from the beginning to the preparation of schools they teach English.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their children and do not have the stress of a delay to go looking for children in a school away from the parent's place of work.
Parents use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty between the employee and the employer is created.
Arch.Design.s is thus registered among companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and who are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens HR marketing.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Look into Gaudi's interiors.
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric sarian, the staircase with a dinosaur spine and the balconies with open fish mouths.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic forms, the house received the nickname of House in bone from the premises.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaics, façade recalling scales and all over present curves, here is all that is ypic for the New Art by Anthony Gaudius.
The front façade of the house runs its dream lines, its pleasant colors and textures that remind nature and animals.
In a more detailed observation we see geometry, rhythm and order thought with precision.
In the night the façade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is reinforced.
Rolling and twisting of shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eye and the blades.
The Battlo house that stands in the Eixample district on Passeig de Gracia market street at number. 43, was born of the construction of an 1877 house by architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a rich entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of old construction and the construction of another new one, but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of unusual reconstruction and better market.
But Casa Battlo's idea as a house with multiple dwellings was not thought of alone by Gaudi.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on its project that decorations were born for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade.
Other artists and creators have also worked for the facade.
The joint work on the plans of Casa Battlo began with successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The premises nicknamed the house hot just after it was finished because of its organic forms "the House in the Bone".
Others, in view of the specific window opening mechanism, called it the "house that dances".
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint Georges the patron of Catalonia.
Other elements of construction sculpture contain hidden religious grounds.
Gaudi has thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time, with air events and typical fireplaces.
Their 45-degree inclination seems strange.
During the Gaudi creation, it was absolutely not in line with the construction directives and it was not allowed to be blocked by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained the building permit from the city, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the completion the municipal council was horrified and demanded changes.
For example, he did not like the members of the municipal council that construction pillars are impeding on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the appeal of Josep Battlo asked (and got satisfaction) for permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common lounge and in the third there was a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented with jewelry.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which you can access to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced by curved walls.
Gaudi also works on the modern concept of space linkage.
The common part can be fully connected by opening the hall doors and high society can communicate comfortably or limit private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi has received in addition to new facades a non-traditional roof and two floors in addition.
Gaudi's game with light is also impressive, blue and white glass tiles with which the interior courtyard is decorated and with light wells.
The two-color game gives maximum light on all floors of the house.
It was simply enough to bet on the principle that white reflects more than the dark that instead absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house that was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund may be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued their visits because they found it to be a lucrative business and they expanded the field of visits to the common spaces and the barn, including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist card holders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the entry price in the other Gaudi buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a friend among the residents of the building and visit the house completely.
